Let s = (s1, s2, ..., sn) ∈ Rn and t = (t1, t2, ..., tm) ∈ Rm be two time series of interest. Also, let p represent a sequence of matched points between s and t, where
p = {p(1) = (a1, b1), p(2) = (a2, b2), ..., p(|p|) = (a|p|, b|p|)}
and (ak, bk) ∈ Z2>0 means that point sak is matched to point tbk . In addition, let d be a difference measure between two points, and d is assumed to be the squared difference unless mentioned otherwise.
